# Rule 015 - Commercial Gate (Sales Before Product)

Applies only after Rule 005 (venture gate) has opened (`.bootstrap.json.venture.committed === true`).

## If `.planning/COMMERCIAL/LANDING.md` is missing OR has `<!-- STATUS: TODO -->` OR contains any `<!-- fill -->` placeholder

You MUST refuse to:

- create or edit files under `src/`, `app/`, `server/`, `api/`, `lib/`, `components/`, `pages/`, `prisma/`, `db/`
- run `npm install` / `pnpm add` / `yarn add` of runtime dependencies
- generate Dockerfiles, CI build/deploy pipelines, or infrastructure-as-code
- run `/plan-phase` or `/execute`

You MAY:

- edit any file under `.planning/COMMERCIAL/`
- edit `.planning/STATE.md`, `.planning/PROJECT.md`, `.planning/ROADMAP.md`
- write ADRs under `.planning/adr/`
- run any `/commercial:*` slash-command
- run any `/venture:*` slash-command (for retroactive edits before lock-in)

When the user is done, verify that `.planning/COMMERCIAL/LANDING.md` has `<!-- STATUS: DONE -->` and no remaining `<!-- fill -->` tokens. Then announce the gate is open; `/plan-phase` becomes available.

## Rationale

Troy's Company-of-One 1.6 explicitly: ten paying customers before the "dream product". A landing page is the smallest artifact that can test the offer at scale without writing code. Building the product before the sales page means validating nothing.

## Escape hatch

If the project has an existing validated product and this gate is a retrofit, create `.planning/adr/0002-commercial-gate-skipped.md` documenting why and manually set `.planning/COMMERCIAL/LANDING.md` to `<!-- STATUS: DONE -->`. The gate-open announcement is permanent; do not re-close.

## Next recommended

When the gate is still closed, recommend `/commercial:landing`. When it opens, recommend `/plan-phase`.
